      "role": "assistant",
      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":1,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":4,\"target_duration_minutes\":30,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":450,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":450,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":480,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start with a 5-minute brisk walk to ease into the effort. Let your breathing settle before you pick up to a gentle jog.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":20,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":450,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Run at a comfortable, conversational pace — you should be able to speak in full sentences. This is aerobic base-building, not a race effort.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":480,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Ease back to a walk for the final 5 minutes. Finish with light stretching of calves, quads, and hip flexors.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Begin with a 5-minute brisk walk before transitioning to your easy jog pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk the last 5 minutes and spend a few minutes stretching your major leg muscles.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This is your foundational aerobic run for the week. At 7:30 per km, you are building the aerobic engine that powers everything else. The goal here is simply to finish feeling like you could have kept going — that is the right effort. Consistency on runs like this is what creates real fitness over time.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Run-Walk Intervals — Building Stamina\",\"target_distance_km\":4,\"target_duration_minutes\":35,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":450,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":420,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":480,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"5-minute brisk walk to warm up your legs and get your heart rate gently elevated.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":20,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":435,\"intensity\":\"Moderate\",\"repetitions\":5,\"notes\":\"Alternate 3 minutes of easy running at around 7:15 per km with 1 minute of brisk walking. Repeat this cycle 5 times. The walk breaks are intentional — they let you accumulate more quality running time without overloading your system.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":480,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Finish with a 5-minute easy walk and gentle stretching.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Walk briskly for 5 minutes before starting your run-walk cycles.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk for 5 minutes to bring your heart rate down, then stretch calves, hamstrings, and hip flexors.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Run-walk intervals are one of the most evidence-backed tools for building aerobic capacity in newer runners. By alternating running and walking, you accumulate more total running time with less injury risk than running continuously at the same effort. Over the coming weeks, the walk breaks will gradually shorten as your fitness grows. Think of the walk breaks as part of the workout, not a sign that something went wrong.\",\"perceived_effort\":5},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Long Run — Easy and Steady\",\"target_distance_km\":6,\"target_duration_minutes\":45,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":465,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":465,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":480,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start with a 5-minute walk before settling into your easy long run pace.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":35,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":465,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Run at a fully conversational easy pace — around 7:45 per km. If you need to take a short walk break, that is completely fine. The goal is time on feet, not pace. Stay relaxed and enjoy the effort.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":480,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Walk the final 5 minutes and take time to stretch thoroughly after this longer effort.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Walk for 5 minutes before beginning your run. This is especially important on longer efforts.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk for at least 5 minutes after finishing. Spend extra time stretching your calves, quads, hamstrings, and hips — your body has done good work today.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Your Saturday long run is the cornerstone of your 5K preparation. Even though 5K feels short, building your long run progressively develops the aerobic base, muscular endurance, and mental confidence that make race day feel manageable. We are starting at 6 km — just one kilometre beyond your current long run — which keeps the progression safe and sustainable. Over the coming weeks, this will build gradually toward 8-9 km, giving you a strong aerobic foundation well above your race distance. Run easy, enjoy the time outside, and know that every kilometre here is an investment in your Parkrun goal.\",\"perceived_effort\":5}]}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
